bioghist.p: Local 99 resulted from mergers in 1974 of various locals whose records are represented here. Seattle (Local 202), and Tacoma (Local 170) are the largest. Bremerton (Local 699), Bellingham (Local 355) and Olympia (Local 142) are also represented in the collection.

scopecontent.p: Minutes, financial records, correspondence, subject series, court papers.

accessrestrict.p: Open to all interested researchers and members of Local 99.

userestrict.p: Creator's literary rights not transferred to the University of Washington Libraries.

processinfo.p: Processing in the form of rehousing in archival containers and additional description paid for by the Labor Archives Fund, Labor Archives of Washington, 2010-2013. Merger of Accessions 3178-001 (Donated by TU Int'l, 4/1/1981) and 3178-002 (Donated by George O. Davis, 10/9/1981). Local 202 is a sub group in boxes 66, 26-40.
